  <title>File</title>

  <para>Files can be stored in Guvnor as assets.</para>

  <para>You need to provide the asset name and file extension in the "New
  Asset" popup dialog.</para>

  <figure>
    <title>Creating a new file asset</title>

    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata align="center" fileref="images/Chapter-Guvnor/NewFile1.png"
                   format="PNG" xml:base="../../"></imagedata>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>

  <para>Once you have created the asset a screen to upload (or download) the
  file itself is shown.</para>

  <figure>
    <title>File upload\download screen</title>

    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata align="center" fileref="images/Chapter-Guvnor/NewFile2.png"
                   format="PNG" xml:base="../../"></imagedata>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>

  <para>If you specify a file extension of "properties" a standard Java
  properties file can also be created.</para>

  <figure>
    <title>Creating a new properties file asset</title>

    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata align="center"
                   fileref="images/Chapter-Guvnor/NewFile-properties1.png"
                   format="PNG" xml:base="../../"></imagedata>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>

  <para>The properties name\value pairs can be maintained from within
  Guvnor.</para>

  <figure>
    <title>Maintaining a properties file</title>

    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata align="center"
                   fileref="images/Chapter-Guvnor/NewFile-properties2.png"
                   format="PNG" xml:base="../../"></imagedata>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>
